  "prompt": "Which are the best IAS coaching institutes in Mumbai?",
  "response": "Mumbai has several reputable coaching institutes for IAS (Indian Administrative Service) preparation. Here are some of the best ones known for their quality of education, faculty, and results:\n\n1. **Raj Malhotra's IAS** - Known for its comprehensive approach to IAS preparation, it offers both online and offline courses, along with test series and study materials.\n\n2. **Vajiram & Ravi** - One of the oldest and most renowned coaching institutes in India for IAS preparation, it has a strong legacy and experienced faculty.\n\n3. **Chandragupta Institute of Management Patna (CIMP)** - Although based in Patna, it has branches in Mumbai and is known for its structured coaching for IAS aspirants.\n\n4. **BYJU's IAS** - Part of the larger BYJU's learning platform, it offers online coaching and has gained popularity due to its interactive video content and personalized learning.\n\n5. **Career Launcher** - It provides IAS coaching through structured programs focusing on both prelims and mains. It also offers test series and doubt-solving sessions.\n\n6. **Sparta IAS** - Known for its rigorous training program and experienced faculty, it caters to both English and Marathi medium students.\n\n7. **Dynasty IAS** - This institute focuses on smaller batch sizes for personalized attention and offers various courses covering all aspects of IAS preparation.\n\n8. **Kalpataru IAS Academy** - It offers comprehensive IAS coaching with a focus on both prelims and mains, conducted by experienced educators.\n\n9. **The Prayas India** - Known for its effective teaching methods and guidance for both preliminary and main examinations.\n\n10. **IAS Gurukul** - Provides quality training and has a good track record of success in various competitive exams.\n\nWhen choosing a coaching institute, it's essential to consider factors such as faculty experience, past results, study materials, batch size, and location. It's also advisable to visit the institutes, attend demo classes, and seek feedback from past students before making a decision.",
